      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Poligon's operational model is characterized by a high degree of directness, providing <cite id=\"10\">direct service delivery</cite> to constituents. This is evidenced by their cost-effectiveness, achieving an impact at approximately <cite id=\"11\">$9.59 per beneficiary</cite>, which is considered exceptional for the advocacy sector. Furthermore, the organization has maintained its <cite id=\"12\">zakat-eligible status</cite> since its early years, providing a unique avenue for Muslim donors to fulfill religious obligations through civic empowerment."
      ],
      "summary": "Poligon Education Fund is a civic engagement organization established in <cite id=\"1\">2017</cite> to empower American Muslim constituents through legislative advocacy and congressional training. The organization focuses on bridging the gap between marginalized communities and the federal government by providing <cite id=\"2\">educational resources and content</cite> that demystify the legislative process. Despite its small financial footprint, Poligon maintains a high level of operational efficiency, directing an <cite id=\"3\">80.0% program expense ratio</cite> toward its core mission. Their primary service delivery model includes <cite id=\"4\">Congressional Advocacy Trainings, Action Alerts, and Policy Briefings</cite>, which are designed to increase the frequency and quality of constituent interactions with elected officials. In 2023, the organization reported <cite id=\"5\">total revenue of $32,150</cite>, reflecting a lean operation that relies heavily on volunteer engagement and targeted outreach. Notably, the charity demonstrates <cite id=\"6\">exceptional fundraising efficiency</cite>, reporting $0.00 spent on fundraising for every $1 raised. This allows the organization to maximize the utility of small-dollar donations for direct advocacy services, such as <cite id=\"7\">voter engagement and legislative briefings</cite>.",
